<p><font face="helvetica" size="12"><b>Solution:</b></font></p>
<p><font color="#980517">on</font> appendSelectionToClipboard</p>
<p>  <font color="#980517">if</font> the <font color="#F88017">selectedText</font> is empty <font color="#68228B">-- there's no selection, so...</font></p>
<p>  <font color="#980517">then</font> <font color="#0000FF">return</font> &quot;Error: no text is selected&quot; <font color="#68228B">-- ...never mind</font></p>
<p>  <font color="#68228B">-- put the selected text at the end of the clipboard:</font></p>
<p>  <font color="#0000FF">set</font> the <font color="#FF0000">clipboardData</font>[&quot;text&quot;] \</p>
<p>     to the <font color="#FF0000">clipboardData</font>[&quot;text&quot;] &amp; <font color="#0000FF">return</font> &amp; the <font color="#F88017">selectedText</font></p>
<p><font color="#980517">end</font> appendSelectionToClipboard</p>